POLICE COMPLAINT FILING PROCEDURE

How to file a complaint:
Step 1: Visit your nearest police station
Step 2: Submit written complaint in duplicate
Step 3: Obtain acknowledgment receipt with unique complaint number
Step 4: You will receive update within 7 days

SOP for Traffic Violations:
- Traffic police can issue e-challan on the spot
- Payment can be done online within 60 days
- Dispute can be raised in traffic court

Citizen Rights:
- Right to get FIR copy for free
- Right to complaint status information
- Right to meet station officer during working hours
